<TD VALIGN="middle" ALIGN="center">

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Irene B. Rosenfeld</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chairman of the Board and</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Chief Executive Officer</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Three Parkway North</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Deerfield, IL 60015</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">March&nbsp;28, 2017 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dear Fellow Shareholders: </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Since we spun off our North American grocery business in 2012 and established Mondel&#275;z International, the world, and our industry, have undergone a period of
unprecedented change. 2016 was yet another example. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">During the year, we successfully navigated an extraordinarily volatile and uncertain environment &#150; slower
GDP growth globally, especially in emerging markets, currency and commodity volatility, market shocks like the Brexit vote and demonetization in India, as well as complex developments in the political landscape, including a growing backlash against
globalization. Through it all, we never lost sight of our vision to build the best snacking company in the world. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In times of rapid change like these, we&#146;re
acting with a sense of urgency to control what we can and create contingencies for what we cannot. Last year, we continued to sharpen our focus on our core snack categories, our Power Brands and key geographies. We also continued to drive down costs
by delivering strong net productivity and improving operational efficiencies throughout the business. Through these actions, we generated the fuel needed to continue to invest for sustainable growth. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">While we&#146;re encouraged by our 2016 performance, we also acknowledge that our top-line growth is not yet where we want it to be. Some of this is due to factors
outside of our control, e.g., a strong dollar, emerging markets GDP, but some is also attributable to mixed execution on our part or deliberate tradeoffs to make our business more profitable. Not all of our actions will pay off immediately, but we
will continue to act boldly and decisively to best position our business for profitable growth over the long term. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">More than ever, I&#146;m convinced that our
results underscore our ability to drive both top- <U>and</U> bottom-line growth. And while today&#146;s market realities may present some near-term hurdles, we remain confident in our ability to deliver on our commitments. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><div style="width:100%;margin-left:0%; margin-right:0%;border:solid 2.00pt;padding-top:2pt;padding-bottom:3pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; padding-top:6pt; margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>YOU&#146;RE INVITED! </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">I&#146;m pleased to invite you to our 2017 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. We will hold the meeting at 9 a.m. CDT on Wednesday,
May&nbsp;17, 2017, at NOAH&#146;s Event Venue in Lincolnshire, Illinois. The venue will open to shareholders at 8&nbsp;a.m. If you wish to attend the meeting, please register in advance by following the instructions included in the Proxy Statement.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1%; margin-right:1%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All shareholders of record as of March&nbsp;8, 2017, are entitled to vote. Even if you plan to attend the meeting in person, we
encourage you to vote in advance in one of three ways: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As we prepare for our Annual Meeting of Shareholders, I&#146;d like to share some highlights of where we&#146;ve been and
where we&#146;re going. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>DELIVERING COMMITMENTS IN A SLOW-GROWTH WORLD </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">I&#146;m proud that we delivered another year of solid results, and I give tremendous credit to my colleagues around the world for their passion, their commitment and
their performance. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">Due to the substantial gain in 2015 from the coffee transactions, our diluted EPS was down 76.4 percent in 2016. However, Adjusted EPS<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> increased 24.1 percent on a
constant-currency basis, driven by our strong operating performance.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">

</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>

Income<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(2)</SUP> margin expanded 230 basis points to 15.3 percent, due to continued reductions in overhead costs and supply chain productivity.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">

<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">2016 net revenues were $25.9 billion, down 12.5 percent, driven by the coffee business transactions, deconsolidation of our Venezuelan operations and currency headwinds. Organic Net Revenue<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> increased 1.3 percent, led by our Power Brands, which grew above category rates.</TD></TR>

</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">We returned $3.7 billion of cash to our shareholders in 2016 in share repurchases and dividends. Since the 2012 launch of the company, we&#146;ve returned $14.8 billion of cash to our shareholders!</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>WE&#146;RE BUILDING A COMPANY THAT WILL THRIVE </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our strategy is guided by our belief that the best companies have been and will continue to be those with the brands, platforms and capabilities to create sustainable
value for shareholders. With our advantaged assets and capabilities, we believe we&#146;re one of the few industry players with the potential to deliver strong top- and bottom-line growth over the long term. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We&#146;re executing on three fronts: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g308532g43i95.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Focus Our Portfolio </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B></B>We continue to
take actions to focus our portfolio on our advantaged snacks categories, which now represent approximately 85 percent of our net revenues, and our Power Brands, like <B></B><I>Oreo</I><B></B>, <B></B><I>belVita</I><B></B>, <B></B><I>Cadbury Dairy
Milk</I><B></B>, <B></B><I>Milka</I><B></B> and <B></B><I>Trident</I><B></B>, which account for nearly 70 percent of our global revenues. Additionally, we continue to seek opportunities to enhance our capabilities and increase our geographic reach.
Last year, we successfully integrated the Kinh Do snacks business, enabling growth in our $200 million Vietnam business, and we recently announced the divesture of our grocery business in Australia and New Zealand. We also expanded the flexibility
and capacity of our allergy-friendly <B></B><I>Enjoy Life</I><B></B> brand, with the opening of a new, state-of-the-art U.S. manufacturing facility. This increased capacity enabled our recent expansion into the U.K. and Australia.<B> </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Reduce Costs </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Cost consciousness
has become part of our DNA, and we&#146;re full steam ahead on cost-reduction initiatives that will drive margin expansion. Last year, we delivered best-in-class net productivity thanks to our supply chain reinvention program, while zero-based
budgeting and our global shared services initiatives continued to provide meaningful overhead cost savings. These cost savings not only fueled our outstanding shareholder returns, but also enabled us to continue to invest for future growth.
We&#146;ve demonstrated our ability to deliver in tough times, and this strong execution gives me great confidence in our ability to deliver on our 17 to 18 percent Adjusted Operating Income margin target in 2018.<SUP
STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(3)</SUP> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Invest for Growth </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The underlying trends and market dynamics that make snacking attractive globally align well to our strengths. We&#146;re not deterred by the short-term challenges facing
our industry and see tremendous growth opportunities ahead of us. We, therefore, continue to leverage our advantaged global footprint and make the necessary investments in our Power Brands, innovation platforms, white-space expansions and
route-to-market capabilities so that we&#146;re well-positioned to accelerate growth as market conditions improve. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>AS OUR CONSUMERS AND CUSTOMERS CHANGE,
WE&#146;RE CHANGING TOO </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">It&#146;s no secret: significant global power shifts are redefining the way our consumers live, eat and shop. But we&#146;re not
standing on the sidelines. We&#146;re on the field, actively analyzing consumer behavior and the impacts of our tactics and investments, and moving quickly and decisively to act on what we learn. We&#146;re following three strategies to accelerate
growth. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="61%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="37%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><B>Contemporizing Our Core</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ROWSPAN="3" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g308532g73k14.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">We&#146;re better connecting our portfolio with today&#146;s consumer. That starts by distorting resources and investment behind our Power Brands, our largest and most profitable trademarks. In 2016, these brands continued to
outpace category growth, led by <I>Oreo</I>, <I>Milka</I> and <I>belVita</I>.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">In addition, our investments in 55 manufacturing Lines of the Future around the world over the past three years have not only driven superior margins, but also enabled greater flexibility to meet evolving consumer needs in terms of
product forms and packaging formats. Today, about half of our Power Brands are produced on advantaged assets, up from only 15 percent in 2013 and on our way to approximately 70 percent by 2018.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Contemporizing our core business also means connecting consumers with our iconic brands through bigger, stronger and more disruptive
ideas. As we generate more cost savings, we&#146;re increasing our marketing investments to bring our spending to leadership levels across our categories. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Filling Key White Spaces </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We&#146;re expanding our Power Brands and
innovation platforms into new geographies and new consumer demand spaces to make our brands available where we&#146;re underrepresented today. Nowhere is this more important than in the rapid growth of the well-being trend. Everywhere, people have
become more attentive to their health and food choices. So, we&#146;re renovating our existing products and introducing new ones that fit how consumers define wellness today. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(3)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The company&#146;s outlook for 2018 Adjusted Operating Income margin is a non-GAAP financial measure that excludes or otherwise adjusts for items impacting comparability of financial results such as restructuring
activities, acquisitions and divestitures. The company is not able to reconcile its full year 2018 projected Adjusted Operating Income margin to its full year 2018 projected reported operating income margin because the company is unable to predict
the timing of its Restructuring Program costs, mark-to-market impacts from commodity and forecasted currency transaction derivative contracts and impacts from potential acquisitions or divestitures. Therefore, because of the uncertainty and
variability of the nature and amount of future adjustments, which could be significant, the company is unable to provide a reconciliation of these measures without unreasonable effort. </TD></TR></TABLE>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Last year, among other initiatives, we launched <I>GOOD THiNS,</I> a delicious snack with no artificial colors and flavors,
no high fructose corn syrup and no partially hydrogenated oils. We&#146;re pleased that it was recently named the No.&nbsp;1 new snacking brand in the U.S.!<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(4)</SUP> </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD VALIGN="top">Building on that momentum, 2017 promises to be an unprecedented year for our well-being innovations, extending across all of our categories and all of our regions.</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top">We recently announced the launch of <I>V&eacute;a</I>, a new premium well-being brand in the savory biscuit segment. Baked with real ingredients and visible herbs, spices and seeds, the recipes are on trend in every way &#150; no
artificial ingredients, colors or flavors, no trans-fat and non-GMO. It will be available in July in the U.S., with additional markets following over time.</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, we also expanded our products into a number of geographic white spaces last year. We&#146;re seeing early success from our
launches of <I>Milka</I> chocolate in China and the repatriation of our <I>Nabisco</I> biscuit trademarks in Japan. We made a big splash into the $14 billion U.S. chocolate market at the end of last year with the introduction of <I>Milka Oreo</I>
chocolate candy bars and <I>Green&nbsp;&amp; Black&#146;s</I> premium chocolate. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top"><B>Driving Selling and Channel Ubiquity</B></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">eCommerce is emerging as the fastest growing channel in the marketplace. As the retail industry continues to undergo transformation, we&#146;re expanding sales and distribution capabilities to ensure that our products are available
wherever and whenever people shop. Our goal is to build an industry-leading eCommerce snacks business, targeting at least $1 billion in revenue by 2020. To reach this goal, we&#146;re investing in stronger capabilities and better
infrastructure.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" ROWSPAN="2" ALIGN="right">


<IMG SRC="g308532g71y10.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top">This past year, we established a dedicated cross-functional team of experienced talent. We improved data analytics, supply chain and digital technologies, optimized our content and search as well as invested in compelling programs
to increase traffic. As we&#146;re implementing these strategies, we&#146;re also accelerating our momentum. Last year, eCommerce net revenues grew more than 35 percent.</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Beyond eCommerce, we&#146;re also boosting our presence in higher growth brick-and-mortar channels, including discounters and
convenience stores in developed markets as well as traditional trade outlets in emerging markets. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>GROWING OUR POSITIVE IMPACT ON THE WORLD AROUND US </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Embedding Sustainability in Our Agricultural Sourcing </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At Mondel&#275;z
International, our growth is directly linked to enhancing the well-being of the people who make and enjoy our products, the communities we serve and our planet as a whole. We&#146;ve launched innovative, industry-leading programs in key commodities
like cocoa, wheat and palm oil. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">


<TR>
<TD WIDTH="18%"></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" WIDTH="1%"></TD>
<TD WIDTH="80%"></TD></TR>


<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="middle"> <P STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.00em; text-indent:-1.00em">


<IMG SRC="g308532g37k27.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</P></TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom">Our 10-year, $400 million Cocoa Life program is empowering more than 200,000 farmers and improving the lives of more than 1&nbsp;million people in key origin markets. Last year, we announced that the Cocoa Life program would be
extended to all <I>Cadbury</I> products by 2019, including those that are currently Fairtrade-certified. For the first time ever, all <I>Cadbury</I> products will be covered by a single sustainable sourcing program &#150; giving our consumers the
confidence that whenever they buy a <I>Cadbury</I> chocolate bar, it will not only taste good but make a difference too.</TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">(4)</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Nielsen Global and H&amp;W Trend Report </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z
INTERNATIONAL </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">With respect to wheat production, our Harmony program promotes biodiversity and good environmental practices across Europe.
The number of wheat farmers committed to follow Harmony agricultural practices &#150; covering the cultivation process from seed to crop &#150; continues to grow. The initial group of 68 farmers in France is now a partnership of more than 1,700
farmers across the continent. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In palm oil, we took steps last year to advance our goal to make sustainable palm oil the mainstream option, based on the principles
that production should be on legally held land, not lead to deforestation or loss of peat land, respect human rights and not use forced or child labor. As part of our updated Palm Oil Action Plan, we laid out new milestones and requirements for
suppliers to work toward a sustainable supply of palm oil. Key new provisions require suppliers to map and assess the risk for all supplying mills on Global Forest Watch, provide assurance that no deforestation occurs on their own concessions and
exclude third-party suppliers who do not immediately cease deforestation and work with recognized third-party experts to protect labor rights. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We recognize
concerns for the welfare of egg-laying chickens and, last year, we announced our decision to fully transition to cage-free eggs in the United States and Canada by 2020 and in Europe by 2025. This move followed years of progress in sustainable and
responsible sourcing. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Helping Consumers Make Mindful Choices with Clear Nutrition Labeling </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To make informed, mindful decisions for themselves and their families, consumers need the right nutritional information delivered in a simple and straightforward manner.
We&#146;re committed to helping our consumers be mindful of how many calories they are taking in and are working to provide clear information about our snacks. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In
the U.S., we&#146;re part of SmartLabel, an initiative created by manufacturers and retailers to enable consumers to get additional details about our products. As such, this year, we were one of the first companies to launch a SmartLabel app,
providing in-store, on-the-spot access to detailed product information for many of our snacking products on smartphones. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In Europe, we recently announced our
support for a pan-European color-coded front-of-pack labeling plan in response to consumer demand for better clarity and more understandable nutritional information. We&#146;ll be working with five other multinationals to put in place a robust
European approach to help consumers make balanced and mindful choices. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>THE PATH AHEAD </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In 2016, our advantaged business model enabled us to deliver another year of Adjusted OI margin expansion, Adjusted EPS growth and strong capital returns. I&#146;m
proud of and inspired by our talented colleagues around the world and proud of our management team for successfully navigating through another challenging environment and continuing to deliver more moments of joy to all of our stakeholders. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Snacking remains an attractive space for growth. It&#146;s a $1.2 trillion market, and while near-term growth may be muted, the underlying trends indicate considerable
runway for our categories to expand further. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">But I also know that we must do more if we want to be the best snacking company in the world. So when the macro
picture improves &#150; and we&#146;re confident it will &#150; the foundation we&#146;re laying today will position us to leverage the investments we&#146;ve made to deliver balanced and sustainable growth on both the top and bottom lines. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:5pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On behalf of our leadership team and our Mondel&#275;z International colleagues around the world, I thank you for another year of support of our company, and for your
belief in our future. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Best regards, </P> <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">


<IMG SRC="g308532g04t70.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g308532g88l57_gray.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P>

INTERNATIONAL </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Forward-Looking Statements </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">This letter to shareholders contains a number of forward-looking statements. Words, and variations of words, such as &#147;will,&#148; &#147;expect,&#148;
&#147;believe,&#148; &#147;would,&#148; &#147;position,&#148; &#147;deliver,&#148; &#147;commitment,&#148; &#147;target&#148; and similar expressions are intended to identify our forward-looking statements, including, but not limited to, statements
about: our future performance, including our future revenue growth, earnings per share and margins; execution of our strategy, including our growth strategies; category growth; market conditions; new products; innovation; our investments and the
results of those investments; growth in and revenues from e-commerce; our well-being initiatives; shareholder value; and our outlook, including 2018 Adjusted Operating Income margin. These forward-looking statements are subject to a number of risks
and uncertainties, many of which are beyond our control, which could cause our actual results to differ materially from those indicated in our forward looking statements. Such factors include, but are not limited to, risks from operating globally
including in emerging markets; changes in currency exchange rates, controls and restrictions; continued volatility of commodity and other input costs; weakness in economic conditions; weakness in consumer spending; pricing actions; unanticipated
disruptions to our business; competition; the restructuring program and our other transformation initiatives not yielding the anticipated benefits; changes in the assumptions on which the restructuring program is based; and tax law changes. Please
also see our risk factors, as they may be amended from time to time, set forth in our filings with the SEC, including our most recently filed Annual Report on Form 10-K. Mondel&#275;z International disclaims and does not undertake any obligation to
update or revise any forward-looking statement in this letter to shareholders, except as required by applicable law or regulation. </P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc308532_1"></A>Proxy Statement Summary </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>In this Proxy Statement Summary and throughout the Proxy Statement, &#147;we,&#148; &#147;us,&#148; &#147;our,&#148; &#147;the Company&#148; and &#147;Mondel&#275;z
International&#148; refer to Mondel&#275;z International, Inc. </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>This summary highlights select information contained elsewhere in this Proxy Statement. You
should read the entire Proxy Statement carefully before voting and consider all information in the Proxy Statement. For more complete information regarding the Company&#146;s 2016 performance, please see the Company&#146;s Annual Report on Form 10-K
for the year ended December&nbsp;31, 2016 (the &#147;2016 Form 10-K&#148;). </I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>2017 Annual Meeting of Shareholders (the &#147;Annual
Meeting&#148;) </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Board Composition: Competencies, Diversity, Refreshment and Tenure </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The composition of the Board taken as a whole enables the Board to represent effectively all shareholders. All 13 director nominees have the personal attributes
including integrity, sound business judgement and vision necessary to establish a competent, ethical and well-functioning board. In addition, the individual director nominees have a variety of backgrounds and experiences that provide the Board with
the key competencies needed for the Board to fulfill its current and future obligations. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Industry Knowledge, Product Development and Marketing Experience: </I>12 of 13 director nominees have <I>s</I>ignificant experience at food and beverage, consumer products and services, or manufacturing companies.
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Operating and Leadership Experience at Complex Organizations: </I>All director nominees have significant strategic, general management and operating experience at major companies or institutions &#150; many with
international reach. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>International Business Experience and Global Perspectives: </I>Over half of the director nominees are living and working or have lived and worked outside of his or her home country; several have lived and worked in
multiple countries and on multiple continents. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

public companies. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Corporate Governance Highlights (Pages 19 and 36 and 91 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We believe that a strong and balanced corporate governance framework is essential to the Company&#146;s long-term success because it promotes the long-term interests of
shareholders, accountability and trust in the Company. We highlight here key aspects of the Company&#146;s corporate governance framework. Shareholders can find additional detail under &#147;Corporate Governance&#148; beginning on page 19 of this
Proxy Statement under &#147;Compensation Discussion and Analysis &#150; Our Executive Compensation Design Principles and Governance Practices Reflect Best Practices to Protect and Promote our Shareholders&#146; Interests&#148; on page 36 of this
Proxy Statement, and under &#147;2018 Annual Meeting of Shareholders&#148; on page 91. </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P><DIV STYLE="position:relative;float:left; width:48%;padding-right:1%;padding-bottom:8pt;overflow:hidden;padding-top:3pt">

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">


<IMG SRC="g308532g01r75_gray.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Annual election </B>of directors (i.e., no staggered Board) </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<IMG SRC="g308532g01r75_gray.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Shareholders of at least 20% of the voting power of the outstanding Common Stock may call <B>a special meeting of shareholders</B> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="27" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">


<IMG SRC="g308532g01r75_gray.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>No &#147;poison pill&#148;</B> (shareholder rights plan) </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><B>Independent leadership of the Board&#146;s work.</B> Our Lead Director has expansive substantive responsibilities and powers, including approval of meeting schedules and agendas </TD></TR></TABLE>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

</TD>

 <P STYLE="font-size:18pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;2. Ratification of the
Selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as Independent Registered Public </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Accountants for Fiscal Year 2017 (Page 75 of this Proxy Statement)
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>


<IMG SRC="g308532g24k20.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 The Board recommends a vote FOR this Proposal </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">As a matter of good governance, we are asking our shareholders to ratify the Audit
Committee&#146;s selection of PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP as the independent registered public accountants for the year ending December&nbsp;31, 2017. We provide information on PricewaterhouseCoopers LLP&#146;s fees in 2016 and 2015 on page&nbsp;29
of this Proxy Statement. </P>

<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px;MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;WIDTH:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;3. Advisory Vote to Approve Executive Compensation (Page 76 of this Proxy Statement)
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>


<IMG SRC="g308532g24k20.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 The Board recommends a vote FOR this Proposal </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Goals </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Human Resources and Compensation Committee (the &#147;Compensation Committee&#148;) has four primary goals for our executive compensation program: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">1.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Attract, retain and motivate talented executive officers and develop world-class business leaders; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">2.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Support business strategies that promote superior long-term shareholder returns; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">3.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align pay and performance by making a significant portion of our Named Executive Officers&#146; (&#147;NEOs&#148;) compensation dependent on achieving financial and other critical strategic and individual goals; and
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="4%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="4%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left">4.</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Align our NEOs&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests through equity-based incentive grants that link executive compensation to sustained and superior Total Shareholder
Return<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> (&#147;TSR&#148;) and stock ownership requirements. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Compensation Design </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We design our executive compensation program to achieve these goals by: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Linking pay to performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Putting pay at risk based on short-term and long-term performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Rewarding long-term sustainable performance; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Targeting pay at or near the median of our peer group; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Setting substantive performance goals; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Requiring executive officers to acquire and hold a significant amount of Common Stock. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>2016 Executive Compensation
Reflected the Performance of our NEOs and the Company </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Cash Incentive Program</I> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">We achieved an above target financial performance rating of 123% under the 2016 Annual Cash Incentive Program. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Despite the challenging top-line environment, we generated strong earnings growth and margin expansion driven by strong operating performance. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">After accounting for financial and individual performance, the awards our NEOs earned were generally slightly above target performance. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Performance Share Units (2014-2016 Performance Cycle</I>) <I> </I></TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

detailed information about our compensation programs and decisions in the Compensation Discussion and Analysis beginning on page 36 and Executive Compensation Tables beginning on page 60 of this Proxy Statement. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">&nbsp;&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="line-height:6.0pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:2pt;border-bottom:1px solid #000000;width:31%">&nbsp;</P>

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>


<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px;MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;WIDTH:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;4. Advisory Vote on the Frequency of Future Advisory Votes to Approve Executive
Compensation (Page 77 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>


<IMG SRC="g308532g24k20.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 The Board recommends a vote for annual (&#147;ONE YEAR&#148;) frequency </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board recommends that shareholders vote to continue
annual (&#147;ONE YEAR&#148;) advisory votes to approve executive compensation (commonly known as &#147;say-on-pay&#148; votes). The Board believes that annual advisory say-on-pay votes provide the Company timely, direct shareholder input regarding
our compensation philosophy, policies and practices. An annual (&#147;ONE YEAR&#148;) advisory say-on-pay vote is consistent with our practice of seeking input from and regularly engaging with our shareholders on corporate governance matters and our
executive compensation program. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>SHAREHOLDER PROPOSALS </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In accordance with U.S. Securities and Exchange Commission (&#147;SEC&#148;) rules, this Proxy Statement includes two shareholder proposals. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;5. Report on Non-Recyclable Packaging (Page 79 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>


<IMG SRC="g308532g24k20.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 The Board recommends a vote AGAINST this Shareholder Proposal </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>ITEM&nbsp;6. Create a Committee to Prepare a
Report Regarding the Impact of Plant Closures on Communities and Alternatives (Page 83 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:10pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>


<IMG SRC="g308532g24k20.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 The Board recommends a vote AGAINST this Shareholder Proposal </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Other Matters that may be Presented at the Annual
Meeting </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Other than Items 1 through 6 described in this Proxy Statement, we do not expect any additional matters to be presented for action at the Annual
Meeting. We described the requirements for shareholders to properly submit proposals and nominations at the 2017 Annual Meeting in the 2016 proxy statement. They are similar to those described under &#147;2018 Annual Meeting of Shareholders&#148; in
this Proxy Statement. The Chairman of the Annual Meeting may refuse to allow presentation of an improperly submitted proposal or a nomination for the Board at the Annual Meeting. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If any other matters properly come before the Annual Meeting, your proxy authorizes the designated proxies to vote on such matters in accordance with their best
judgment and in their discretion. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Advance Voting Methods (Page 88 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P>

12 on page 88 of this Proxy Statement for additional details). If you are voting via the Internet or by telephone, be sure to have your proxy card or voting instruction form (&#147;VIF&#148;) in hand and follow the instructions. You can vote in
advance of the meeting any of three ways: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Voting Instructions to Proxies </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">At the Annual Meeting, the persons named as proxies on each shareholder&#146;s proxy card will vote the shares represented by the proxy card FOR or AGAINST or ABSTAIN
from voting with respect to each of the nominees listed in proposal 1 and with respect to proposals 2, 3, 5 and 6 and for ONE YEAR, TWO YEARS or THREE YEARS or ABSTAIN from voting with respect to proposal 4, as indicated in the shareholder&#146;s
voting instructions. If no indication is made on the properly executed proxy card, proxies will vote FOR each of the director nominees listed in proposal 1, FOR proposals 2 and 3, ONE YEAR with respect to proposal 4 and AGAINST proposals 5 and 6 and
in their discretion upon such other business as properly comes before the meeting. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Voting at the Annual Meeting (Page 88 of this Proxy Statement)
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">All shareholders of record as of March&nbsp;8, 2017 may vote in person at the Annual Meeting. Generally, beneficial shareholders may vote in person at the
Annual Meeting if they have a legal proxy. See Question 12 on page 88 of this Proxy Statement for detailed information. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Attending the Annual
Meeting &#150; Important Note about Advance Registration Process and Admission Requirements (Page 90 of this Proxy Statement) </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">If you plan to attend the Annual
Meeting in person, see Question 21 on page 90 of this Proxy Statement for important details about advance registration and admission requirements. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>Asking Questions at the Annual Meeting </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Shareholders will
have the opportunity to ask questions or make comments related to the matters being voted on and more generally about the Company and its business. They may do so at the times and in the manner indicated in the meeting agenda and meeting procedures
that we will distribute at the Annual Meeting registration desk and according to the Chairman&#146;s instructions. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To assist us in preparing to answer shareholder
questions at the Annual Meeting, we request that shareholders who register to attend the Annual Meeting submit any questions they would like to ask at the Annual Meeting at least 10 days before the date of the Annual Meeting. Please: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<div style ="BORDER-BOTTOM:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-LEFT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-RIGHT:1.00pt solid #000000;BORDER-TOP:1.00pt solid #000000;MARGIN-LEFT:0px;MARGIN-RIGHT:0px;WIDTH:100%"><div style="width:97%; margin-top:1.5%; margin-left:1.5%; margin-right:-1.25%">

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>In Memory of Stephen Frasier Bollenbach </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B>1942 &#150; 2016 </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On October&nbsp;8, 2016, the Board lost a
great friend and remarkable colleague. Steve Bollenbach joined the Board in October 2012, when the Company spun off its North American grocery business to create Kraft Foods Group. His remarkable career in the family entertainment, media,
hospitality, real estate and financial services industries, included senior roles at a number of major companies, among them Marriott Corporation, The Walt Disney Company and Hilton Hotels Corporation. While serving on the Company&#146;s Board, he
used his vast knowledge and experience to make many contributions to the Company&#146;s success and the Board&#146;s effectiveness. He was relied upon to share powerful insights, distill complex situations, ask tough questions and, always, to speak
his mind. He is missed greatly. </P>
 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P></div><br clear="All"></div><br clear="All">

 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z
INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;8 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc308532_2"></A>ITEM&nbsp;1. Election of Directors </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:24pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_3"></A>Process for Nominating Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee identifies, evaluates and recommends to the Board director nominees for election at the Annual Meeting (and any adjournments or postponements
of the Annual Meeting). The Governance Committee invites director nominee suggestions from the directors, management, shareholders and others. In addition, the Governance Committee has retained a third-party executive search firm to assist it in
identifying and evaluating potential director nominees based on the Board&#146;s recruitment objectives. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>General Qualifications for Nomination to the Board
</B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes all directors should possess certain attributes, including integrity, sound business judgment and vision, as these characteristics are
necessary to establish a competent, ethical and well-functioning board that best represents shareholders&#146; interests. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Consistent with the Corporate Governance
Guidelines (the &#147;Guidelines&#148;), when evaluating the suitability of an individual for nomination, the Governance Committee considers that individual&#146;s: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">general understanding of the varied disciplines relevant to the success of a large, publicly traded company in today&#146;s global business environment; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">understanding of the Company&#146;s global businesses and markets; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">professional expertise and educational background. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee also considers: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">other factors that promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience, including, among others, gender, race and national origin; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether the individual meets various independence requirements, including whether an individual&#146;s service on boards and committees of other organizations is consistent with our conflicts of interest policy; and
</TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether the individual can devote sufficient time and effort to fulfill his or her responsibilities to the Company given the individual&#146;s other commitments. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Board Composition: Director Competencies, Experiences and Expertise </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
Governance Committee works with the Board to determine the appropriate mix of competencies that will result in a Board that is strong in its collective knowledge, enabling the Board to fulfill its responsibilities and best perpetuate the
Company&#146;s long-term success and represent all shareholders&#146; interests. Based upon its discussions with the Board, the Governance Committee has identified these key competencies that are particularly desirable in order for the Board to
fulfill its current and future obligations: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">

Development/Innovation</I></P></TD></TR>
<TR BGCOLOR="#e5e5e5" STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><I>Public Company Board and Corporate Governance Experience</I> at large publicly traded companies providing directors with a solid
understanding of their extensive and complex oversight responsibilities and furthering the goals of greater transparency, accountability for management and the Board and protection of shareholders&#146; interest</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>

<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<I>CEO/COO/Other Governance Leadership
Positions</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<I>Government Affairs/Regulatory</I></P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-left:8pt"><I>Academic and Research Experience</I> provides strong critical thinking and verbal communication skills as well as a greater diversity of
views and thought processes</TD>
<TD VALIGN="bottom" STYLE="BORDER-LEFT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD VALIGN="top" STYLE="BORDER-RIGHT:1px solid #bfbfbf; BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #bfbfbf; padding-right:2pt">
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<I>Talent Assessment and People
Development/Compensation</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:2.25em; text-indent:-2.25em; font-size:8pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<I>Research &amp;
Development/Innovation</I></P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee&#146;s director recruitment planning considers both the evolving needs of the Company and Board as well as the
impact of anticipated departures on the Board&#146;s future composition and leadership of the Board. Based on that work, the Committee most recently sought to identify and recruit a sitting or recently retired CEO of a global manufacturing company
with significant experience in cost management. That search identified Charles E. Bunch, who has significant experience in cost management and is a highly capable global executive and seasoned public company director. Mr.&nbsp;Bunch was recommended
to the Governance Committee as a potential director by Nelson Peltz, an incumbent non-employee director, and also by the Governance Committee&#146;s consultant in connection with the Governance Committee&#146;s search. The Board appointed
Mr.&nbsp;Bunch effective September&nbsp;1, 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual Director Self-Assessments and Considerations for Renomination of Incumbent Directors </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee coordinates annual Board, committee and director self-assessments. The assessment process includes one-on-one discussions between each director
and the Chair of the Governance Committee. Annually, the director nominees complete questionnaires to update and confirm their background, qualifications and skills and identify any potential conflicts of interest. The Governance Committee assesses
the experience, qualifications, attributes, skills, diversity and contributions of each director. The Governance Committee also considers each individual in the context of the Board composition as a whole, with the objective of recruiting and
recommending a slate of director nominees who can best perpetuate the Company&#146;s success and represent our shareholders&#146; interests through the exercise of sound judgment and informed decision-making. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Board Refreshment, Director Tenure and Age Limits </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that
its composition should provide continuity as well as new experiences and fresh perspectives relevant to the Board&#146;s work. The Board does not believe that directors should expect to be automatically renominated. Therefore, the annual Board and
director self-assessment processes are important determinants in a director&#146;s renomination and tenure. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;10 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">In addition, as amended during 2016, the Guidelines provide that: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All non-employee directors will have a term limit of 15 years. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Non-employee directors will not be nominated for election to the Board after their 75th birthday. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:6pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">However, if a non-employee director aged 70 to 75 is appointed or elected to the Board, then that director will have a term limit of five years. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The current Board composition reflects the Board&#146;s commitment to ongoing refreshment: five of the independent director nominees served as directors before we
spun-off Kraft Foods Group, Inc. to shareholders on October&nbsp;1, 2012; seven joined the Board on or after October&nbsp;1, 2012. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:24pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt" ALIGN="center">


<IMG SRC="g308532g90x20.jpg" ALT="LOGO">
 </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Board Diversity </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mondel&#275;z
International has cross-cultural and diverse employees manufacturing and marketing delicious snack food and beverage products for consumers in approximately 165 countries around the world. The Board embraces and encourages the Company&#146;s and
Board&#146;s culture of diversity and inclusion. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Although the Board does not establish specific goals with respect to diversity, the Board&#146;s overall diversity
is an important consideration in the director recruitment and nomination process. The Guidelines provide that when evaluating the suitability of individuals for nomination, the Governance Committee considers criteria including, among others, gender,
race and national origin as they promote diversity of views, knowledge and experience that contribute to a more informed and effective decision-making process. As part of its annual assessment of the Board&#146;s composition, the Governance
Committee assesses the effectiveness of the Board&#146;s efforts to promote diversity in all its forms. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Four of the director nominees are women, including the
Chairman and CEO; the director nominees represent varied ages (as of March&nbsp;8, 2017): 55 to 75, races and national origins, and bring diverse life and professional experiences. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;11 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>The Governance Committee Welcomes Shareholder Recommendations for Candidates for Election to the Board </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee will consider recommendations for director candidates submitted by a shareholder(s). The shareholder(s) should submit to the Corporate Secretary
both the recommended candidate&#146;s name along with the same information required for a shareholder to nominate a candidate for election to the Board at an Annual Meeting and in the same manner as set forth in the advance notice provisions of the
Company&#146;s By-Laws (the <FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">&#147;By-Laws&#148;).</FONT> </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee evaluates director candidates recommended by
shareholder(s) using the same criteria as it uses to evaluate candidates whom the Governance Committee identifies (described above). The Governance Committee makes a recommendation to the Board regarding the candidate&#146;s appointment or
nomination for election to the Board. The Board considers the Governance Committee&#146;s recommendation, and then decides whether to appoint or nominate the candidate. The Corporate Secretary advises the shareholder(s) of the Board&#146;s decision
whether to appoint or nominate the candidate. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Shareholders Elect Directors Annually </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each member of the Board is elected annually by a majority of votes cast (if the election is uncontested). The terms of all directors elected at the 2017 Annual Meeting
will end at the 2018 Annual Meeting of Shareholders or when a director&#146;s successor has been duly elected and qualified. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee recommended
and the Board nominated for election at the 2017 Annual Meeting each of the 13 incumbent directors listed below under &#147;&#150;&nbsp;Director Nominees for Election at the Annual Meeting.&#148; Of the 13&nbsp;director nominees standing for
election, shareholders elected 12 to one-year terms at the 2016 Annual Meeting of Shareholders. The Board appointed Mr.&nbsp;Bunch, the 13<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">th</SUP> director nominee, to the Board effective
September&nbsp;1, 2016. Mr.&nbsp;Bollenbach, whom shareholders elected at the 2016 Annual Meeting of Shareholders, passed away in October 2016. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Each director
nominee consented to his or her nomination for election to the Board and to serving on the Board, if elected. If a director nominee should become unavailable to serve as a director, the persons named as proxies intend to vote the shares for a
replacement director nominee designated by the Board. In lieu of naming a substitute, the Board may reduce the number of directors on the Board. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_4">
</A>Director Nominees for Election at the Annual Meeting </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Individual Nominees&#146; Experience, Qualifications, Attributes and Skills </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that each director nominee for election at the Annual Meeting is highly qualified. All 13 director nominees satisfy the criteria stated in the
Guidelines and possess the personal attributes essential for the proper and effective functioning of the Board. The director nominees&#146; biographies describe the specific qualifications that the Governance Committee relied upon when determining
whether to recommend the individual director nominees for election and led the Board to nominate him or her for election. The biographies also include information about current and past (covering the last five years) directorships at companies
publicly listed in the U.S. and registered investment companies. A particular director nominee may have experience and qualifications in addition to those described in the biographies below, including service on the boards of various private
companies, companies listed outside of the U.S. and charitable, educational and cultural institutions. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;12 </FONT></P>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>THE BOARD RECOMMENDS SHAREHOLDERS VOTE FOR THE ELECTION OF EACH OF THE 13 DIRECTOR NOMINEES LISTED BELOW. </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The following information regarding each director nominee is as of March&nbsp;8, 2017.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" ALIGN="center">

<TD WIDTH="12%"></TD>

<TD WIDTH="10%"></TD>

<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="8" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-TOP:1px solid #000000">&nbsp;</TD></TR>
