<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>LEWIS W.K. BOOTH,</B> Former Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, Ford Motor Company</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since October 2012; Independent</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Booth, 68, served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of the Ford
Motor Company (&#147;Ford&#148;), a global automobile manufacturer, from November 2008 until his retirement in April 2012. He was Executive Vice President of Ford of Europe, Volvo Car Corporation and Ford Export Operations and Global Growth
Initiatives, and Executive Vice President of Ford&#146;s Premier Automotive Group from October 2005 to October 2008. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Booth held various executive leadership positions with Ford, including Chairman and Chief Executive Officer
of Ford of Europe, President of Mazda Motor Corporation and President of Ford Asia Pacific and Africa Operations. He worked for Ford in various positions from 1978 to 2012. Mr.&nbsp;Booth was appointed Commander of the Order of the British Empire in
June 2012 for his services to the United Kingdom&#146;s automotive and manufacturing industries.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During his career at Ford, Mr. Booth gained global business
experience. He led operations in Africa, Asia and Europe. In these and other roles, he successfully implemented major growth initiatives, business restructuring and cost management and was involved in strategy, product development, marketing and
operations.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Booth held a variety of positions in Ford&#146;s
Finance staff. As Ford&#146;s Chief Financial Officer during the 2008 financial crisis, Mr. Booth led a restructuring of Ford&#146;s balance sheet and a return to growth and profitability.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Booth is a Chartered Management Accountant.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. Booth also has extensive public company board and
corporate governance experience. He is a director of Gentherm Incorporated and Rolls-Royce Holdings plc.</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>NELSON PELTZ,</B> Chief Executive Officer and Founding Partner, Trian Fund Management, L.P.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since January 2014; Independent</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Peltz, 74, has served as Chief Executive Officer and Founding Partner of Trian Fund
Management, L.P. (&#147;Trian&#148;), an alternative investment management firm, since November 2005. He also served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Triarc Companies, Inc. (now known as The Wendy&#146;s Company), a holding company for
various consumer and industrial businesses, from April 1993 to June 2007, and has served as its non-executive Chairman since June 2007. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Peltz served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Trian Group, Limited Partnership,
which provided investment banking and management services to entities controlled by Mr.&nbsp;Peltz and Peter May, from January 1989 to April 1993 and as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Triangle Industries, Inc., a manufacturer of packaging
products, from 1983 to December 1988.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Peltz has extensive investment, financial and
leadership experience as Trian&#146;s Chief Executive Officer and as non-executive Chairman (and formerly as the Chairman and Chief Executive Officer) of The Wendy&#146;s Company, working with management teams and boards of directors, as well as in
acquiring, investing in and building companies and has strong relationships with institutional investors, investment banking/capital markets advisors and others that can be drawn upon for the Company&#146;s benefit.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Peltz brings considerable experience in the food
and beverage and consumer products industry through his service on the board of directors of H.J. Heinz Company, Sysco Corporation and The Wendy&#146;s Company.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Peltz also has extensive public company board
and corporate governance experience. In addition to serving as a director of Sysco Corporation and The Wendy&#146;s Company, he is also a director of The Madison Square Garden Company. He was formerly a director of H.J. Heinz Company, Legg Mason,
Inc. and Ingersoll-Rand plc. The National Association of Corporate Directors recognized Mr.&nbsp;Peltz in 2010, 2011 and 2012 as among the most influential people in the global corporate governance arena.</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>FREDRIC G. REYNOLDS,</B> Former Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer, CBS Corporation</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since December 2007; Independent</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds, 66, served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of CBS
Corporation (&#147;CBS&#148;), a mass media company, from 2006 until his retirement in 2009. From 2001 through 2005, Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds served as President and Chief Executive Officer of Viacom Television Stations Group and as Executive Vice
President and Chief Financial Officer of Viacom Inc. (&#147;Viacom&#148;), a mass media company, from 2000 to 2001. He also served as Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer of CBS and its predecessor, Westinghouse Electric Corporation,
from 1994 to 2000. Prior to that, Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds served in various capacities at PepsiCo, a food and beverage company, for twelve years, including Chief Financial Officer or Financial Officer at Pizza Hut, Pepsi Cola International, Kentucky Fried
Chicken Worldwide and Frito-Lay.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds has extensive experience in both the
media (including, advertising and marketing) and the food and beverage industries. He served in various roles, including as President, Chief Executive Officer, Executive Vice President and Chief Financial Officer at CBS, Viacom and PepsiCo. While at
CBS, he successfully managed the integration following the CBS/Viacom merger and he was ultimately responsible for all financial functions and growing portfolio at Viacom. During his tenure as Chief Financial Officer of CBS, CBS shareholders
experienced substantial share appreciation and return of capital.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds brings extensive financial experience
gained during his service as Chief Financial Officer at CBS and a Financial Officer at Viacom and at divisions of PepsiCo.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds is a Certified Public Accountant.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Reynolds also has extensive public company board
and corporate governance experience. He is a director of Hess Corporation and United Technologies Corporation. He was formerly a director of AOL, Inc.</P></TD></TR>

<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since June 2006</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld, 63, was appointed Chief Executive Officer and a director of Mondel&#275;z
International in June 2006 and became Chairman of the Board in March 2007. Prior to that, she served as Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Frito-Lay, a division of PepsiCo, from 2004 to 2006. Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld was employed by Mondel&#275;z
International and its predecessor companies in various capacities from 1981 until 2003, including President of Kraft Foods North America and President of Operations, Technology, Information Systems and Kraft Foods, Canada, Mexico and Puerto
Rico.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld possesses invaluable perspective and
experience as current Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Mondel&#275;z International and former Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of the Frito-Lay division of PepsiCo. She led the restructuring and turnaround of key businesses, the
acquisition of Cadbury and the successful spin-off of Kraft Foods&#146; North American Grocery business.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld has extensive knowledge of the food and beverage industry and a history of bringing consumer focus and innovation to building successful global brands. She also led
accelerated growth in better-for-you products and developed a pipeline of health and wellness offerings. Her extensive corporate insight is a result of long-term service in various positions, including key executive roles at Mondel&#275;z
International and its predecessor companies and at PepsiCo.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld has extensive public company board and
corporate governance experience. She has served on the Board since 2006.</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:10.00em; text-indent:-10.00em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>CHRISTIANA&nbsp;S.&nbsp;SHI,&nbsp;&nbsp;</B>Former President, Direct-to-Consumer of Nike,
Inc.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since January 2016; Independent</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Shi, 57, served as President, Direct-to-Consumer of Nike, Inc. (&#147;Nike&#148;), a
global provider of athletic footwear and apparel, from July 2013 until her retirement in September 2016. From 2012 to 2013, she served as Nike&#146;s Vice President and General Manager, Global Digital Commerce. From 2010 to 2012, she served as
Nike&#146;s Chief Operating Officer for Global Direct-to-Consumer.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Prior to joining Nike,
Ms.&nbsp;Shi spent 24 years at McKinsey&nbsp;&amp; Company (&#147;McKinsey&#148;), a global management consulting firm, in various roles including ten years as Director and Senior Partner.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">From July 1981 to July 1984, Ms.&nbsp;Shi served in various trading, institutional sales and
investment banking roles at Merrill Lynch&nbsp;&amp; Company.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director
Qualifications:</I></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;During her career at McKinsey,
Ms.&nbsp;Shi worked across North America, Europe, Latin America and Asia providing leadership, expertise and strategic vision to senior executives of Fortune 200 consumer companies. She designed and led performance transformation programs, developed
cross-channel marketing and merchandising programs, and drove market entry work.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;In her various roles at Nike, Ms.&nbsp;Shi led
Nike&#146;s global integrated digital commerce strategy and retail organization, as well as real estate, finance, supply chain operations and information technology.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;With her deep knowledge of digital commerce, Ms.&nbsp;Shi
grew Nike&#146;s digital commerce capabilities.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Ms.&nbsp;Shi also has extensive public company board and
corporate governance experience. She is a director of West Marine, Inc.</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>PATRICK T. SIEWERT,</B> Managing Director and Partner, The Carlyle Group, L.P.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since October 2012; Independent</P></TD></TR>

<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Siewert, 61, has served as a Managing Director and Partner for The Carlyle Group, L.P.
(&#147;Carlyle&#148;), a global alternative asset management firm, since April 2007.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">From 2001
to 2007, he held a variety of roles with The Coca-Cola Company (&#147;Coca-Cola&#148;), a global beverage company, including Group President and Chief Operating Officer, Asia and a member of the Global Executive Committee.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">From 1974 to 2001, he held a variety of roles with Eastman Kodak Company (&#147;Eastman
Kodak&#148;), a technology company focused on imaging products and services, including Chief Operating Officer, Consumer Imaging and Senior Vice President and President of the Kodak Professional Division.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;While working at Coca-Cola, Eastman Kodak and Carlyle,
Mr.&nbsp;Siewert developed extensive knowledge about the food and beverage and consumer products industries, especially insights into consumer trends and routes to market.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Siewert led business operations in Europe,
Africa, and the Middle East and most recently in Asia where he focuses on opportunities and challenges in Asian markets.</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;Siewert also has extensive public company board and corporate governance experience. He is a director of Avery Dennison Corporation.</P></TD></TR>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>RUTH J. SIMMONS, </B>President Emerita, Brown University</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since October 2012; Independent</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Dr.&nbsp;Simmons, 71, is President Emerita of Brown University, having served as President from
2001 to 2012. Prior to that, Dr.&nbsp;Simmons served as President of Smith College from 1995 to 2001 and Vice Provost of Princeton University from 1991 to 1995. She served in various leadership positions at colleges and universities beginning in
1977, including the University of Southern California from 1979 to 1983, Princeton University from 1983 to 1989 (and again from 1991 to 1995) and Spelman College from 1989 to 1991.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Dr.&nbsp;Simmons has over 25 years in leadership roles at
Brown University, Princeton University and Smith College. In these roles, she was responsible for leading and managing large, complex institutions of higher education and for the development of student and faculty talent. She provides valuable
perspective to our Governance Committee and is well-positioned to advise the Board and its committees on matters relating to our people.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Dr.&nbsp;Simmons has had a distinguished career in
academic research and leadership in the field of higher education for which she has been frequently honored. Dr.&nbsp;Simmons is a fellow of the American Academy of Arts and Sciences, a member of the American Philosophical Society and the Council on
Foreign Relations. She has been knighted by the President of France as a chevalier of the French Legion of Honor for advancement of French arts and culture.</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Dr.&nbsp;Simmons also has extensive public company board
and corporate governance experience. She is a director of Fiat Chrysler Automobiles NV and Square, Inc. and was formerly a director of Chrysler Group LLC and Texas Instruments Incorporated.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;18 </FONT></P>

<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>JEAN-FRAN&Ccedil;OIS M. L. VAN BOXMEER,</B> Chairman of the Executive Board and Chief Executive Officer,
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;
&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Heineken&nbsp;N.V.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Director since January 2010; Independent</P></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="font-size:1pt">
<TD HEIGHT="13" COLSPAN="5"></TD></TR>
<TR STYLE="page-break-inside:avoid ; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt">
<TD VALIGN="top" COLSPAN="5" STYLE="BORDER-BOTTOM:1px solid #000000"> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;van Boxmeer, 55, has been Chairman of the Executive Board and Chief Executive Officer of
Heineken N.V. (&#147;Heineken&#148;), a global brewing company with a global network of distributors and brewers in more than 70 countries, since 2005 and a member of its Executive Board since 2001. He has been employed by Heineken, in various
capacities since 1984.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><I>Director Qualifications:</I></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;As Chairman and Chief Executive Officer of Heineken,
Mr.&nbsp;van Boxmeer led Heineken&#146;s significant global expansion, bringing Heineken&#146;s iconic brands into new markets &#150; most notably into Asian markets. He has a strong track record leading strategic acquisitions and integrations and
driving revenue growth.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr. van Boxmeer brings a global perspective with
particular insights regarding developing markets.</P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT
 COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;van Boxmeer has extensive leadership experience, including global operations, product development and marketing, and the beverages and consumer products industries.</P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:1pt; margin-left:1.80em; text-indent:-1.80em; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Mr.&nbsp;van Boxmeer also has extensive public company
board and corporate governance experience. He is a Member of the Shareholders&#146; Committee of Henkel AG&nbsp;&amp; Co. KGaA.</P></TD></TR>
</TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc308532_5"></A>Corporate Governance </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We
believe that having and adhering to a strong corporate governance framework is essential to our long-term success. This section describes our governance policies, key practices, Board leadership structure and oversight functions. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_6"></A>Governance Documents </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">To learn more
about our corporate governance practices, you can access the following corporate governance documents at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/investors/corporate-governance</U></I>. We will also provide copies of any of these documents to
shareholders upon written request to the Corporate Secretary. </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">You can access our employee Code of Conduct (&#147;Code
of Conduct&#148;) at <I><U><FONT STYLE="white-space:nowrap">www.mondelezinternational.com/about-us/compliance-and-integrity</FONT></U></I>. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_7">
</A>Governance Guidelines </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board adopted the Guidelines articulating our governance philosophy, practices and policies in a range of areas, including: the
Board&#146;s role and responsibilities; Board composition and structure; responsibilities of the committees of the Board; CEO and Board performance evaluations; and succession planning. At least annually, the Governance Committee reviews the
Guidelines and recommends any changes to the Board for its consideration. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;19 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_8"></A>Key Elements of Corporate Governance Framework </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Election of Directors</I>. The By-Laws provide that the shareholders elect all directors annually. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I></I><I>Proxy Access By-Law Provisions</I>. Key parameters: </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Minimum Ownership Threshold: 3% or more of the outstanding Common Stock; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Ownership Duration: continuously for at least 3 years; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Nominating Group Size: no more than 20 shareholders may aggregate holdings to meet the minimum ownership threshold; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Maximum Nominations Permitted: <I>greater of</I> 20% of the Board or 2 nominees. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Majority and Confidential Voting in Uncontested Director Elections with a Director Resignation Policy</I>. The By-Laws provide that, in an election in which the number of nominees for election equals the number of
directors to be elected, director nominees must be elected by a majority of the votes cast. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Special Meetings of Shareholders</I>. The By-Laws allow shareholders of record of at least 20%&nbsp;of the voting power of the outstanding stock to call a special meeting of shareholders. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Limitation on Management Directors</I>. The Guidelines provide that the Chairman and CEO generally should be the only member of management to serve as a director. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Director, Committee and Board Independence</I>. 12 of the 13 director nominees are independent. All Board committees consist entirely of independent directors. (See &#147;&#150; Director Independence&#148; on page 22
for more information about the Board&#146;s process for determining director independence.) </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Leadership Structure.</I> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">An independent director serves as Lead Director and has expansive substantive responsibilities and powers, including approval of meeting schedules and agendas; </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Independent directors chair the Board&#146;s four standing committees; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="10%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The CEO serves as Chairman of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:4pt; margin-bottom:0pt; text-indent:10%; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">See additional discussion below under &#147;&#150; Board
Leadership Structure.&#148; </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Executive Sessions</I>. At each in-person Board meeting, the independent directors meet without the CEO or any other members of management present to discuss substantive issues important to the Company, including
matters concerning management. Generally, the Lead Director chairs these sessions. A committee chair leads Board discussion of a topic relevant to that committee&#146;s remit. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Annual Board, Committee and Director Self-Assessments.</I> In consultation with the Lead Director, the Governance Committee establishes and oversees processes for annual Board and committee self-assessments and
coordinates individual director self-assessments. The directors&#146; self-evaluation process includes candid, one-on-one discussions between the Chair of the Governance Committee and each independent director. The Board, committees and management
use the results of these self-assessments in planning their work, ensuring director accountability, Board composition analysis and director recruitment decisions, governance decisions, and planning meetings and agendas. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Shareholder Engagement</I>. Consistent with our shareholder engagement philosophy, we engage with shareholders to seek their input on emerging issues and to address their questions and concerns. During the year, we
engaged with a diverse mix of shareholders on a wide range of topics including, among others, strategy, capital allocation, business performance, executive compensation, corporate governance, sustainability and corporate social responsibility. These
exchanges were candid and constructive. The Lead Director is available for consultation with our major shareholders. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"> <P ALIGN="left" STYLE=" margin-top:0pt ; margin-bottom:0pt; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt"><I>Strategic Planning and Risk Oversight. </I>Annually, the Board meets with management to discuss, understand and
challenge our strategic plan&#146;s short-term and long-term objectives. At its meetings during the balance of the year, the Board and management track progress against the strategic plan&#146;s goals, consider opportunities in light of
circumstances in the food and beverage industry and the economic environment, and monitor strategic and operational risks. The Company&#146;s goals and executive compensation design are tied to a number of metrics critical to achieving the strategic
plan and promoting long-term shareholder returns. More generally, the Board is responsible for oversight of strategy, broad corporate policy and overall performance of the Company through engaged oversight of management.
</P></TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;20 </FONT></P>

before deciding her performance rating and compensation actions. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Director Stock Ownership Guidelines</I>. <I></I> </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">To promote alignment of directors&#146; and shareholders&#146; interests, we expect directors to hold Common Stock in an amount equal to five times the annual Board retainer within five years of joining the Board. As of
March&nbsp;8, 2017, all directors with at least five years of service on the Board met or exceeded this requirement. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Special Meetings of the Board</I>. The By-Laws empower either the Lead Director or the Chairman to call special meetings of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top"><I>Limits on Board Memberships. </I>The Guidelines provide that a director who is also a sitting CEO should not serve on the boards of directors of more than two public companies, including the Company&#146;s Board.
Other directors should not serve on the boards of directors of more than four public companies, including the Company&#146;s Board. All of our directors are in compliance with this policy. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_9"></A>Board Leadership Structure </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The
By-Laws provide the Board flexibility in determining its leadership structure. The Board may appoint and designate the duties of a Lead Director and permit one person to hold the offices of both Chairman and CEO. Within that framework, the Board
annually re-evaluates its leadership structure to determine the most appropriate leadership structure at that time. In considering which leadership structure will allow it to most effectively carry out its responsibilities and best represent
shareholders&#146; interests, the Board takes into account various factors. Among them are our specific business needs, our operating and financial performance, industry conditions, economic and regulatory environments, the results of Board and
committee annual self-assessments, the advantages and disadvantages of alternative leadership structures based on circumstances at that time and our corporate governance practices. In keeping with this principle, the Board may determine that the CEO
also serves as Chairman, but if it does so, it also appoints an independent Lead Director with substantive responsibilities. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Current Leadership </B></P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">An independent director, Mr.&nbsp;Ketchum, serves as Lead Director; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Independent directors chair the Board&#146;s four standing committees; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The CEO, Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld, serves as Chairman of the Board. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that this leadership structure
provides an effective balance of strong leadership and independent oversight and best meets the Board&#146;s current circumstances and anticipated needs. The Board also believes that this leadership structure enhances its oversight of risk
management because the CEO, who is ultimately responsible for the Company&#146;s risk management process, is in the best position as Chairman to discuss with the Board key risks and management&#146;s responses to them. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Independent Director Leadership and Oversight </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board believes that
independent Board leadership and oversight are very important. Therefore, it established the substantive and expansive position of independent Lead Director for times when one individual serves as both Chairman and CEO. The independent directors
annually select the Lead Director for a one-year term. The Board created the Lead Director position to provide independent leadership of the Board&#146;s affairs on behalf of shareholders, increase the Board&#146;s effectiveness, promote open
communication amongst the independent directors and serve as the principal liaison between the Chairman and the other independent directors. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;21 </FONT></P>

<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Serve as liaison between the independent directors and the Chairman and CEO; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">

Board review and approval; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Be available for consultation with the Company&#146;s major shareholders; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Perform such other duties as the Board may from time to time delegate to the Lead Director. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Mr.&nbsp;Ketchum is the
Lead Director. The independent directors first appointed him to that role in 2009 and have re-appointed him annually. The independent directors believe that he is an effective Lead Director due to his independence, leadership, global operating
experience and corporate governance experience. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Chairman and CEO Role and Responsibilities </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld has served as the CEO and as a director since June 2006. In conjunction with the Company&#146;s 2007 spin-off from Altria Group, Inc., the Board
concluded that Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld should also serve as Chairman because of her extensive knowledge of the Company, the food industry and the competitive environment in which we operate, her leadership experience and her ability and dedication to
working closely with the Lead Director and the other independent directors. Based on current circumstances and anticipated needs, the Board continues to believe that having Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld serve as both Chairman and CEO promotes
shareholders&#146; interests and contributes to the Board&#146;s efficiency and effectiveness. The Board believes that she is generally in the best position to inform the independent directors about our global operations and critical business
matters including the Company&#146;s risk management process, and ensure alignment of our business and strategic plans. Further, the Board believes that combining these roles also expedites communication between Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld and the Board.
</P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_10"></A>Director Independence </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>All
directors are independent except for Ms.&nbsp;Rosenfeld, our Chairman and CEO </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board determined that, under the Board&#146;s categorical standards and
NASDAQ&#146;s listing standards, the following directors are independent: Lewis W.K. Booth, Charles E. Bunch, Lois D. Juliber, Mark D. Ketchum, Jorge S. Mesquita, Joseph Neubauer, Nelson Peltz, Fredric G. Reynolds, Christiana S. Shi, Patrick T.
Siewert, Ruth J. Simmons and Jean-Fran&ccedil;ois M. L. van Boxmeer. In addition, Stephen F. Bollenbach was independent during the portion of 2016 he served on the Board. Irene B. Rosenfeld is not independent because she is a Mondel&#275;z
International employee. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Guidelines require that at least 80% of the directors meet the NASDAQ listing standards&#146; independence requirements. In order to
determine that a director is independent, the Board must affirmatively determine, after reviewing all relevant information, that a director has no relationship with Mondel&#275;z International or any of its subsidiaries that would interfere with the
exercise of independent judgment in carrying out the responsibilities of a </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;22 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">
director. To assist in this determination, the Board adopted categorical standards of director independence, including whether a director or a member of the director&#146;s immediate family has
any current or past employment or affiliation with Mondel&#275;z International or the independent registered public accountants. These standards are generally consistent with the NASDAQ listing standards&#146; independence requirements. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_11"></A>Oversight of Risk Management </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our
business faces various risks, including strategic, financial, operational and compliance risks: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Management is responsible for the day-to-day assessment, management and mitigation of risk. Identifying, managing and mitigating our exposure to these risks and effectively overseeing this process are critical to our
operational decision-making and annual planning processes. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Board has ultimate responsibility for risk oversight, but it has delegated primary responsibility for overseeing risk assessment and management to the Audit Committee. Pursuant to its charter, the Audit Committee
reviews and discusses risk assessment and risk management guidelines, policies and processes utilized in our Enterprise Risk Management (&#147;ERM&#148;) process. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Our ERM process is ongoing and implemented at all levels of our operations and across business units to identify, assess, monitor, manage and mitigate risk. Our ERM
process facilitates open communication between management and the Board so that the Board and committees understand key risks to our business and performance, our risk management process and how it is functioning, the participants in the process and
the information gathered through the process. The Audit Committee annually reviews the functioning of our ERM process as well as the results of our annual ERM risk assessment. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Annually, the Audit Committee reviews and approves management&#146;s recommendation for allocating to the full Board or another committee or retaining for itself
responsibility for reviewing and assessing key risk exposures and management&#146;s response to those exposures. Management provides reports to the Board and the appropriate committee in advance of meetings regarding key risks and the actions
management has taken to monitor, control and mitigate these risks. Management also attends Board and committee meetings to discuss these reports and provide any updates. The committees report key risk discussions to the Board following their
meetings. Board members may also further discuss the risk management process directly with members of management. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;23 </FONT></P>

Compensation-Related Risk.&#148; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_12"></A>Codes of Conduct </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have
adopted the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors. It fosters a culture of honesty and integrity, focuses on areas of ethical risk, guides non-employee directors in recognizing and handling ethical issues and provides
mechanisms to report unethical conduct. Annually, each non-employee director must acknowledge in writing that he or she has received, reviewed and understands the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Code of Conduct </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We have adopted the Code of Conduct that applies to all of
our employees. It includes policies that cover ethical and legal practices for every aspect of the business. The Code of Conduct reflects values and contains important rules employees must follow when conducting business. The Code of Conduct is part
of our global compliance and integrity program. The program provides training throughout the Company and encourages reporting of wrongdoing by offering anonymous reporting options and a non-retaliation policy. </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">We will disclose in the Corporate Governance section of our website any amendments to the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors or Code of
Conduct and any waiver granted to an executive officer or director under these codes. </P>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;24 </FONT></P>


<p Style='page-break-before:always'>
<HR  SIZE="3" style="COLOR:#999999" WIDTH="100%" ALIGN="CENTER">
<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_13"></A>Review of Transactions with Related Persons </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Related Persons Policy and Procedures </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Board has adopted a written policy
regarding &#147;related person transactions.&#148; In general, &#147;related persons&#148; are the following persons and their immediate family members: directors, executive officers and shareholders beneficially owning more than 5% of the
outstanding Common Stock. A related person transaction is one in which Mondel&#275;z International is a participant, the amount involved exceeds $120,000 and any related person had, has or will have a direct or indirect material interest. The
Governance Committee reviews transactions that might qualify as related person transactions. If the Governance Committee determines that a transaction qualifies as a related person transaction, then the Governance Committee reviews and approves,
disapproves or ratifies the transaction. The Governance Committee approves or ratifies only those related person transactions that are fair and reasonable to Mondel&#275;z International and in our shareholders&#146; best interests. When it is not
practicable or desirable to delay review of a transaction until a committee meeting, the chair of the Governance Committee reviews and approves or ratifies potential related person transactions and reports to the Governance Committee any transaction
so approved or ratified. When reviewing and acting on a related person transaction under this policy, the Governance Committee considers, among other things: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">its commercial reasonableness; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">the materiality of the related person&#146;s direct or indirect interest in it; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether it may involve an actual, or create the appearance of a, conflict of interest; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">its impact on the related person&#146;s independence (as defined in the Guidelines and the NASDAQ listing standards); and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">whether it would violate any provision of the Code of Business Conduct and Ethics for Non-Employee Directors or the Code of Conduct. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Any member of the Governance Committee who is a related person with respect to a transaction under review may not participate in the deliberations or decisions
regarding the transaction. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL"><B>Review of Related Persons Transactions Since January&nbsp;1, 2016 </B></P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:6pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">On January&nbsp;25, 2017, BlackRock, Inc. (&#147;BlackRock&#148;), an investment management corporation, filed a Schedule 13G/A with the SEC reporting that it was a
greater than 5% shareholder of the Company as of December&nbsp;31, 2016. During 2016, BlackRock acted as an investment manager with respect to certain investment options under our U.S. retirement savings plans and Canadian, Irish and U.K. pension
plans. BlackRock was selected as an investment manager by each plan&#146;s designated authority for plan investments. BlackRock&#146;s selection was based on the determination of each plan&#146;s designated authority that the selection met
applicable standards and that the fees were reasonable and appropriate. BlackRock&#146;s fees, approximately $1.9 million during 2016, were paid from the plan assets of the specific plans for which it performed services. The plans expect to pay
similar fees to BlackRock during 2017 for similar services. (Fees, based on plan asset value, are paid quarterly on a lagging basis.) </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_14">
</A>Communications with the Board </B></P> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Information for shareholders and other parties interested in communicating with the Lead Director, the Board or the
independent directors, individually or as a group, is available at <I><U>www.mondelezinternational.com/Investors/corporate-governance#contacts</U>.</I> The Corporate Secretary: </P>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">forwards communications relating to matters within the Board&#146;s purview to the Lead Director or appropriate independent director(s) and communications relating to matters within a Board committee&#146;s area of
responsibility to the chair of the appropriate committee; </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">forwards communications relating to ordinary business matters, such as suggestions, inquiries and consumer complaints, to the appropriate Mondel&#275;z International executive or employee, but makes them available to
any independent director who requests them; and </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">does not forward or retain solicitations, junk mail and frivolous or inappropriate communications. </TD></TR></TABLE>
 <p STYLE="margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt ; font-size:8pt">&nbsp;</P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:9pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="right"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">MONDEL&#274;Z INTERNATIONAL&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;25 </FONT></P>

<h5 align="left"><a href="#toc">Table of Contents</a></h5>

 <P STYLE="margin-top:0pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:16pt; font-family:ARIAL"><A NAME="toc308532_15"></A>Board Committees and Membership </P>
<P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">The Governance Committee considers and makes recommendations to the Board regarding the Board&#146;s committee structure and membership. The committee structure and
membership is as follows: </P> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Board establishes committee structure and designates the committee members and chairs following consideration of the Governance Committee&#146;s recommendations. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">The Board has adopted a written charter for each standing committee. The charters define each committee&#146;s roles and responsibilities. </TD></TR></TABLE>
<P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Independent directors comprise 100% of the Audit, Compensation, Finance and Governance Committees. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">All committee chairs are independent. Committee chairs approve agendas and materials for their committee meetings. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Each committee meets regularly in executive session without management. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="font-size:4pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:10pt" BORDER="0" CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" WIDTH="100%">
<TR style = "page-break-inside:avoid">
<TD WIDTH="6%">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD WIDTH="3%" VALIGN="top" ALIGN="left"><FONT COLOR="#4c4c4c">&#149;</FONT></TD>
<TD WIDTH="1%" VALIGN="top">&nbsp;</TD>
<TD ALIGN="left" VALIGN="top">Committees may retain outside legal, financial and other advisors at the Company&#146;s expense. </TD></TR></TABLE> <P STYLE="margin-top:12pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:10pt; font-family:ARIAL">Throughout 2016, the
Board had, and currently has, four standing committees: Audit, Finance, Governance and Compensation. </P> <P STYLE="margin-top:18pt; margin-bottom:0pt; font-size:12pt; font-family:ARIAL" ALIGN="center"><B><A NAME="toc308532_16"></A>Committee
Membership<SUP STYLE="font-size:85%; vertical-align:top">(1)</SUP> </B></P> <P STYLE="font-size:12pt;margin-top:0pt;margin-bottom:0pt">&nbsp;</P>
<TABLE CELLSPACING="0" CELLPADDING="0" WIDTH="100%" BORDER="0" STYLE="BORDER-COLLAPSE:COLLAPSE; font-family:ARIAL; font-size:8pt">
